Furneaux makes haec relate to Livia (the younger), which is hardly possible, seeing that the last person mentioned is Agrip- pina; it is clear, too, that Livia was a mere tool, and that it was Sejanus, not she, who made use of the callidi criminatores. Madvig corrects to alitque3 Orelli, more probably, con- strues haec as a neuter plural, gov- erned by some such word as egit.
